with the newer XTI library.  The @cite{tiuser.h} header file is for directly passing TPI service
primitives to and from the Transport provider using @manpage{getpmsg(2)} and @manpage{putpmsg(2s)}.

@subsection Kernel Space Drivers and Modules

Typical include files for writing @dfn{STREAMS} module and drivers implementing transport providers
in kernels space include @cite{tihdr.h} or @cite{tpi.h}.  Both header files provide access to
definitions for the TPI interface and additional XTI definitions for use by @dfn{STREAMS} drivers
and modules.  Additional header files for interacting with specific drivers or modules may also be
required.

Aside from including these header files, the general procedures for compiling @dfn{STREAMS} modules
and drivers also apply to @dfn{STREAMS} modules and drivers written to the Transport Provider
Interface.  Examples can be found in the @file{strinet-@value{VERSION_STRINET}},
@file{strsctp-@value{VERSION_STRSCTP}} and @file{striso-@value{VERSION_STRISO}} packages that
implement a number of transport providers.

