The @cite{@value{PACKAGE_TITLE}} package is compliant to a number of standards specifications as
follows:

@node TPI Compatibility
@section TPI Compatibility

The Transport Provider Interface provided by the @cite{@value{PACKAGE_TITLE}} package is compliant
with XPG3, XPG4, and the Transport Provider Interface (TPI) Revision 1.5 (from UNIX International)
and Transport Provider Interface (TPI) Revision 2.0.0. (from The Open Group).

Conformance of the @manref{tirdwr(4)} read write cooperating module mentioned in the TPI
specification is tested for compliance with the @manref{test-tirdwr(8)} test case executable and the
@command{autotest} test suite.
See @refman{Conformance Test Programs}, for more information.

@node XTI Compatibility
@section XTI Compatibility

The X/Open Transport Interface provided by the @cite{@value{PACKAGE_TITLE}} package is compliant
with XPG3, XPG4, and the X/Open Transport Interface present in X/Open Networking Services Release
4.2 (XNS 4.2) and X/Open Networking Services Release 5.2 (XNS 5.2), part of the standards necessary
for UNIX '95 branding.

Conformance of the package to the XTI specification is tested using the @manref{test-xnet(8)} and
@manref{test-xnet_thr(8)} test case executables and the @command{autotest} test suite.  Both
native and 32-bit compatibility modes over 64-bit native kernels are tested by these test suites.
Also, the @manref{test-timod(8)} test case executable, and the @command{autotest} test suite, test
the XTI library cooperating module, @manref{timod(4)} for compliance.
See @refman{Conformance Test Programs}, for more information.

@node TLI Compatibility
@section TLI Compatibility

The X/Open Transport Interface is not compatible with the older AT&T UNIX System Laboratories
Transport Layer Interface (TLI) in a number of respects where the TLI differs from the XTI.
Nevertheless, the older TLI declarations are also provided in the @file{tiuser.h} header file.

